### Sprint Reporter - Example Requests
### Use with REST Client extension in VS Code

# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Health Check
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Check service health
GET http://localhost:3200/health

# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Generate Reports
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Generate JSON report for last week
POST http://localhost:3200/api/reports/sprint
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "startDate": "2026-04-14",
  "endDate": "2026-04-21",
  "projectName": "asset-management",
  "format": "json"
}

### Generate HTML report for entire sprint
POST http://localhost:3200/api/reports/sprint
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "startDate": "2026-04-01",
  "endDate": "2026-04-14",
  "projectName": "asset-management",
  "format": "html"
}

### Generate report for custom period
POST http://localhost:3200/api/reports/sprint
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "startDate": "2026-03-15",
  "endDate": "2026-04-21",
  "projectName": "asset-management",
  "format": "json"
}

# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Error Cases (for testing)
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Invalid date format
POST http://localhost:3200/api/reports/sprint
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "startDate": "invalid-date",
  "endDate": "2026-04-14",
  "projectName": "asset-management",
  "format": "json"
}

### Start date after end date
POST http://localhost:3200/api/reports/sprint
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "startDate": "2026-04-14",
  "endDate": "2026-04-01",
  "projectName": "asset-management",
  "format": "json"
}

### Missing project name
POST http://localhost:3200/api/reports/sprint
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "startDate": "2026-04-01",
  "endDate": "2026-04-14",
  "projectName": "",
  "format": "json"
}
